{"id": "EUVD-2025-25097", "enisaUuid": "bc054d63-9916-3f32-b87d-4fa52a52e5e4", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nvirtio-net: fix recursived rtnl_lock() during probe()\n\nThe deadlock appears in a stack trace like:\n\n  virtnet_probe()\n    rtnl_lock()\n    virtio_config_changed_work()\n      netdev_notify_peers()\n        rtnl_lock()\n\nIt happens if the VMM sends a VIRTIO_NET_S_ANNOUNCE request while the\nvirtio-net driver is still probing.\n\nThe config_work in probe() will get scheduled until virtnet_open() enables\nthe config change notification via virtio_config_driver_enable().", "datePublished": "2025-08-16T12:30:33", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-18T18:32:49", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/4e7c46362550b229354aeb52038f414e231b0037", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/3859f137b3c1fa1f0031d54263234566bdcdd7aa", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/be5dcaed694e4255dc02dd0acfe036708c535def", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-38551"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-38551"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "04dd235e-223f-3faf-a5f7-1676e59eecbd", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "df28de7b00502761eba62490f413c65c9b175ed9 <3859f137b3c1fa1f0031d54263234566bdcdd7aa"}, {"id": "1da957e4-922d-3d15-806d-9c4963ea907d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.16"}, {"id": "39b021a4-5e21-3f8e-a8da-8040ca93f442", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "3f2fde27-d4dd-3495-946c-e35b5bdcebe6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "df28de7b00502761eba62490f413c65c9b175ed9 <be5dcaed694e4255dc02dd0acfe036708c535def"}, {"id": "50ce2cca-8276-398a-9eb4-8a40b7ba0ba9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.12"}, {"id": "86f83b43-58e5-3929-83d8-dec6d1bb5b29", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "df28de7b00502761eba62490f413c65c9b175ed9 <4e7c46362550b229354aeb52038f414e231b0037"}, {"i